<!-- §8 Why people are buying -->
<h2>Why Is Everything Under My Sink a Disaster?</h2>
<p>The under-sink cabinet is the most neglected storage space in most kitchens — and for one reason: the pipe. Standard shelf inserts don't account for P-traps or garbage disposals, so they either don't fit or leave a dead zone of unusable floor space. Most people give up and just pile things on the cabinet floor until something spills.</p>
