<!-- §11 How to use -->
<h2>How to Set It Up in Under 5 Minutes</h2>
<div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.25rem;margin:1.25rem 0;">
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">1</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Measure before you buy</strong><p>Open your cabinet and check your interior width and pipe location. The organizer adjusts from 15" to 25" wide — if your cabinet is narrower than 15" or wider than 25", this won't fit. Note whether your P-trap is centered or offset; the U-shaped shelf handles both.</p></div></div>
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">2</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Adjust legs and shelf height</strong><p>Slide the legs to your cabinet width. Then choose from four height positions — you want at least 1" of clearance above your drain pipe. The shelf clicks into position; no tools needed. The whole adjustment takes about 90 seconds.</p></div></div>
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">3</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Load strategically</strong><p>Put the tallest items (dish soap, spray cleaners) on the lower tier where there's more vertical clearance. Use the upper tier for medium-height items. Stash small loose things (rubber gloves, sponge pads, drain plugs) in the pull-out drawer so they stop disappearing to the back of the cabinet.</p></div></div>
</div>

